<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: What workflow and equipment for ROM dev and hacking?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10876&amp;p=123649#p123649"><![CDATA[
Paul at infiniteneslives.com sells single-game flash carts, the same kind that you'll probably use to make your finished product. Near the end, once your game is in late beta, try your release candidate builds on those. Make sure to test power cycles and resets, as there are several different micro-alignments between CPU and PPU timing that could screw things up.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Jan 11, 2014 2:41 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
